        "text": "Note: Feature available only for Contract Managers and Service and Contract Managers.\n*1.* Go to Product Database\n*2.* Click in New button and a button will open\n*3.* Fill in all the fields: \n -* Contract:* select the contract related to the product. If you didn't create the contract yet, click on “New Contract” and a new contract form will open.  Follow the instructions from step How to create a new contract? \n -* Product Name:* enter a name to this product, related to a product that is described in the contract. \n - *Category:* select the correct category related to the described product in the contract. \n - *Type:* select if the product is fixed (it’s the same amount for every time you are been charge) or variable (if it depends on the quantity) \n -*Start/End Date:* dates related to the product. It should be within same start and end date from contract\n - *Fixed Quantity:* if the product is fixed, fill this information. Add the fixed quantity related to the product. \n - UoM: select the correct description for this product\n - Price: this is the unit price of the product as mentioned in the contract document. It is the price for each specific item described in the contract.\n - Period: it’s the frequency in which the price and the quantity are described for PxQ. Options: daily, weekly, monthly, quarterly, yearly, one time, other. \n - Status: estimate (for contracts in draft mode), active (for active contracts), inactive (for inactive contracts)\n*4.* Click Save button and a new product is created\n*5.* If you want to create more products, click Save & New, a new form will open. ",
